description.narrative: 1. The civic education programme trained 300 young people from the governorates of Giza, Menufiyya and Faoyum. 2. Danish Egyptian Political Party Network continued capacity development and the exchange programme for youth politicians representing Egyptian and Danish political parties. 3. Female parliamentarians trained in cooperation with American University in Cairo. 4. Annual Youth Exchange Programme organised a youth conference in cooperation with the Swedish Institute in Alexandria, gathering 40 young people from Europe and the Middle East to discuss topics such as gender and politics.

1. Two passages renovated in the Downtown area to support participatory ways of renovating and revitalizing public space. 2. Digital and interactive presentation of the history of Cairo developed. 3.
